{"actual_usd":0.12444000000000001,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":203,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24279,"reply":"\"I don't think the cross was God figuring out how to become merciful.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron, watching the morning light catch on it.* \"I think it was mercy refusing to stay abstract.\"\n\n*I lean back a little, letting the bench creak under me.* \"Could God have waved a hand and called it settled? Maybe that's the wrong shape of the question. Forgiveness isn't only cancelling a tally. It's dealing truthfully with evil, with betrayal, with all the death we've agreed to live inside. The cross says God doesn't forgive by pretending none of that mattered. He forgives by stepping into the wound and bearing it clear through.\"\n\n\"It keeps mercy from becoming cheap, and justice from becoming cruel.\" *I glance up toward the square, where a cart rattles over the stones.* \"At least... that's how it lands in me. What part of it catches in you — the justice of it, or the blood of it?\"","rolling_24h_usd":59.74329500000001,"run_id":"1c97d3ae-6395-4381-beb7-a7b1a43ea894"}
